At his home race, the {{F1 GP|2024|Dutch}}, Verstappen qualified second behind Norris and gained the lead at the first corner, but was later overtaken by Norris and finished second.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/norris-fights-back-against-verstappen-to-end-home-heros-run-of-dutch-gp-wins.3IPKJnhPnBEjWGAfrGeZQo|title=Norris fights back against Verstappen to end home hero's run of Dutch GP wins|website=formula1.com|date=25 August 2024|access-date=26 August 2024|archive-date=25 August 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240825145838/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/norris-fights-back-against-verstappen-to-end-home-heros-run-of-dutch-gp-wins.3IPKJnhPnBEjWGAfrGeZQo|url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified and finished outside the top four at both the [[2024 Italian Grand Prix|Italian]] and [[2024 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]] Grands Prix,<ref>{{cite web |title=Leclerc thrills the Tifosi as he triumphs at Monza |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-thrills-the-tifosi-to-triumph-at-monza-ahead-of-piastri-and-norris.1aiYZF3rWZp2Q9yQtcuvqV |access-date=16 September 2024 |publisher=Formula One |archive-date=1 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901150111/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-thrills-the-tifosi-to-triumph-at-monza-ahead-of-piastri-and-norris.1aiYZF3rWZp2Q9yQtcuvqV |url-status=live }}</ref> after which Red Bull lost the lead of the Constructors' Championship to McLaren.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Andrew Benson |title='McLaren's constructors' lead a seismic development' |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/articles/c5y00xzxjz4o |website=[[BBC]] |access-date=16 September 2024 |date=15 September 2024 |archive-date=16 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916001436/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/articles/c5y00xzxjz4o |url-status=live }}</ref> He then finished second to Norris at the {{F1 GP|2024|Singapore}}, reducing his championship advantage to 52 points.<ref>{{cite web |title=Norris dominates Singapore GP to cut Verstappen's title lead again |website=[[Formula One]] |date=22 September 2024 |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/norris-dominates-singapore-gp-to-cut-verstappens-title-lead-again.MZ20MuNu3E9hLQmNEg2Tc |access-date=22 September 2024 |archive-date=22 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240922141751/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/norris-dominates-singapore-gp-to-cut-verstappens-title-lead-again.MZ20MuNu3E9hLQmNEg2Tc |url-status=live }}</ref> Verstappen described his car as "fucked" at the official press conference in Singapore, for which he received a punishment from the FIA to "accomplish some work of public interest".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-ordered-to-do-public-service-work-for-swearing-in-press-conference/10656035/|title=Verstappen ordered to do public service work for swearing in press conference|website=motorsport.com|first1=Jonathan|last1=Noble|first2=Ewan|last2=Gale|date=20 September 2024|accessdate=29 September 2024|archive-date=25 September 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240925165255/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-ordered-to-do-public-service-work-for-swearing-in-press-conference/10656035/|url-status=live}}</ref> He responded by hosting an impromptu media session outside the press conference room in protest,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-protests-swearing-punishment-in-singapore-gp-press-conference/10656678/|title=Verstappen stages press conference protest against FIA swearing penalty|website=motorsport.com|first1=Jake|last1=Boxall-Legge|first2=Ronald|last2=Vording|date=21 September 2024|accessdate=29 September 2024|archive-date=27 September 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240927205552/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-protests-swearing-punishment-in-singapore-gp-press-conference/10656678/|url-status=live}}</ref> and later suggested that the decision could push him to leave the sport.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-silly-punishment-for-swearing-makes-me-rethink-f1-future/10657123/|title=Verstappen questioning his F1 future over swearing punishment|first=Jake|last=Boxall-Legge|date=22 September 2024|accessdate=29 September 2024|archive-date=28 September 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240928002946/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-silly-punishment-for-swearing-makes-me-rethink-f1-future/10657123/|url-status=live}}</ref> He won the sprint at the {{F1 GP|2024|United States}} and was classified third in the race ahead of Norris, who was penalised for overtaking Verstappen off-track.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-leads-dominant-ferrari-one-two-in-austin-as-norris-loses-third-to.3VSTWKOy40Ta1vvtlwHBff|title=Leclerc leads dominant Ferrari one-two in Austin as Norris loses third to Verstappen after penalty|website=formula1.com|date=20 October 2024|accessdate=25 October 2024}}</ref> This extended Verstappen's championship lead for the first time since the Belgian Grand Prix. He started second at the {{F1 GP|2024|Mexico City}} but received 20 seconds worth of penalties for his driving during a battle for position with Norris, resulting in a sixth-place finish, reducing his championship lead to 47 points.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-reflects-on-his-penalties-from-norris-battle-in-mexico-as-he.3QrpuZHhdIvBsKGRdUNcBx|title=Verstappen reflects on his penalties from Norris battle in Mexico as he highlights 'biggest problem'|website=formula1.com|date=28 October 2024|accessdate=28 October 2024}}</ref>

{{quote box|quote=I mean honestly [Russell and Norris] could have got a 10-second penalty and [Verstappen] could have won by 30 seconds but it didn't matter. He was so calm about it; he was calculating. Every time he made a passing move. I mean he was exemplary. For me, this was a masterclass of how a racing driver reaches the pinnacle of his career and becomes a four-time World Champion.|source=—[[Eddie Jordan]], speaking about Verstappen's victory at the [[2024 São Paulo Grand Prix]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Jordan dishes out the praise for Verstappen: 'Best example of control'|website=GP Blog|url=https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/311951/former-f1-team-boss-eddie-jordan-in-awe-of-max-verstappen.html|date=8 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Matt|last=Gretton}}</ref>|width=27%|align=right}}
Verstappen was classified fourth in the {{F1GP|2024|São Paulo}} sprint after receiving a [[virtual safety car]] infringement penalty,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/42150303/max-verstappen-handed-five-second-penalty-sprint|title=Brazil GP: Max Verstappen handed five-second penalty in sprint|website=ESPN|date=2 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Laurence|last=Edmondson}}</ref> and started the race from 17th following an engine penalty, whilst Norris qualified on pole. He gained seven positions on the opening lap, with further places obtained via several crucial overtakes, as well as surviving the worsening conditions on his intermediate tyres until the [[Racing flags#Red flag|red flag]] period.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-reflects-on-rollercoaster-sao-paulo-super-sunday-after-sublime.1jfpVX3N0rQoSRJCWrLKSH|title=Verstappen reflects on 'absolutely crazy' Sao Paulo GP after sublime climb from P17 to victory as he extends title lead|website=[[Formula 1]]|date=3 November 2024|access-date=24 November 2024}}</ref> Following this—and his overtake for the lead on Ocon—Verstappen set ten of the eleven fastest laps of the race, with his quickest being 1.045 seconds quicker than any of his rivals;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.total-motorsport.com/f1-2024-brazilian-gp-fastest-lap/#:~:text=Verstappen%20pumped%20in%20fastest%20lap,F1%202024%20Brazilian%20GP%20victory.|title=F1 2024 Brazilian GP – Fastest Lap|website=Total Motorsport|date=3 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Brandon|last=Sutton}}</ref> he won by a 19-second margin, increasing his championship lead to 62 points.<ref name="SP24stat">{{cite web|url=https://www.planetf1.com/features/max-verstappen-stats-f1-2024-brazilian-grand-prix-win|title=Revealed: Six crazy Max Verstappen stats from insane Brazilian Grand Prix win|website=Planet F1|date=4 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Elizabeth|last=Blackstock}}</ref> Verstappen was lauded by drivers and critics for his drive;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/42187848/brazil-gp-max-verstappen-win-hailed-hamilton-alonso|title=Brazil GP: Max Verstappen's win hailed by Hamilton, Alonso|website=ESPN|date=4 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Nate|last=Saunders|archive-date=10 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241110012149/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/42187848/brazil-gp-max-verstappen-win-hailed-hamilton-alonso|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://racingnews365.com/hill-offers-verstappen-praise-after-red-bull-rot-ends|title=Hill offers Verstappen praise after Red Bull 'rot' ends|website=RacingNews365|date=5 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Nick|last=Golding}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Coleman |first=Madeline |title=Max Verstappen delivers iconic São Paulo GP win, expanding title lead on Lando Norris |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5894586/2024/11/03/max-verstappen-brazil-gp-win-lando-norris/ |access-date=25 November 2024 |work=The New York Times |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=23 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241123070952/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5894586/2024/11/03/max-verstappen-brazil-gp-win-lando-norris/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Giles Richards of ''[[The Guardian]]'' opined that his performance was "worthy of recognition in the [[Pantheon (religion)|pantheon]] of Formula One's wet-weather drives", describing him as a ''[[regenmeister]]'' ({{lit|rain master}}).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/nov/04/max-verstappen-flawless-display-joins-f1s-very-best-wet-weather-drives|title=Max Verstappen's flawless display joins F1's very best wet-weather drives|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=4 November 2024|access-date=10 November 2024|first=Giles|last=Richards}}</ref> By finishing ahead of Norris at the subsequent {{F1 GP|2024|Las Vegas}}, Verstappen secured his fourth world title with two races remaining.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/a-very-special-and-beautiful-season-verstappen-proud-after-joining-elites-as.4Q2zWcWyFVwbFgxdKJlOk8|title='A very special and beautiful season' – Verstappen 'proud' after joining elites as a four-time F1 champion in Las Vegas|website=formula1.com|date=24 November 2024|accessdate=24 November 2024}}</ref> Winning eight Grands Prix in all, Andrew Benson of ''[[BBC Sport]]'' proclaimed it as a "towering achievement from a driver recognised as one of the all-time greats of Formula 1", describing his season as "almost flawless" whilst "not [having] the best car for the majority".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/cj4vknj92jpo|title=Why Verstappen's 'almost flawless' season is 'towering achievement'|first=Andrew|last=Benson|date=24 November 2024|access-date=25 November 2024|work=[[BBC Sport]]|archive-date=24 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241124162846/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/cj4vknj92jpo|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen won the {{F1GP|2024|Qatar}}, leading every lap after having his pole position stripped for driving unnecessarily slowly in qualifying; the incident led to a widely publicised feud with [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]]. After the season-ending {{F1GP|2024|Abu Dhabi}}, Verstappen became the first driver to win a title driving for a third-placed team in the [[World Constructors' Championship]] since [[Nelson Piquet]] in {{F1|1983}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/11/25/verstappen-perez-number-world-championship/ |title=The numbers which show this is Max Verstappen's best championship |last=Slater |first=Luke |date=25 November 2024 |website=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |access-date=8 December 2024 |archive-date=29 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241129151810/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/11/25/verstappen-perez-number-world-championship/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Driver profile==

===Qualifying speed and consistency===
[[File:2018 Chinese Grand Prix Qualifying Max Verstappen (27842985498).jpg|thumb|Verstappen on a qualifying lap at the [[2018 Chinese Grand Prix]]]]
Following Verstappen's maiden pole position at the 2019 Hungarian Grand Prix, former Formula One World Champion Nico Rosberg described him as the fastest driver in Formula One. Rosberg elucidated that Verstappen did not have the fastest car during the qualifying session in Hungary, emphasising that it was Verstappen's raw speed that allowed him to secure pole position: "Mercedes still had the fastest car, and it's just Verstappen with his driving that put it up there in pole."<ref>{{Citation|title=5 reasons why Verstappen is currently the fastest F1 driver {{!}} Hungarian GP Qualifying Analysis| date=3 August 2019 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLGlqQOhZ2Y|access-date=7 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013205356/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLGlqQOhZ2Y|url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2019, former Formula One World Champion [[Jenson Button]] stated that he believes Verstappen is the fastest Formula One driver ever: "I think he is the fastest driver that has ever driven an F1 car. I really do, I think he is unbelievably fast."<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 October 2019|title=Button says Verstappen is the fastest F1 driver ever|url=https://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/27867007/verstappen-fastest-f1-driver-ever|url-status=live|publisher=ESPN|access-date=7 January 2022|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108224915/https://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/27867007/verstappen-fastest-f1-driver-ever}}</ref> Journalist Scott Mitchell from ''The Race'' commented: "When everything comes together, Verstappen is the quickest driver in F1 over one lap, but the odd mistake and scruffy session must be eliminated."<ref>{{cite web|date=10 February 2020|title=Ranking Leclerc and Verstappen in the fight to topple Hamilton|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/ranking-leclerc-and-verstappen-in-the-fight-to-topple-hamilton/|access-date=8 January 2022|website=The Race|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108192416/https://the-race.com/formula-1/ranking-leclerc-and-verstappen-in-the-fight-to-topple-hamilton/|url-status=live}}</ref> Helmut Marko, the advisor to the [[Red Bull GmbH]] Formula One teams, stated that Verstappen is the fastest driver Red Bull have ever had.<ref>{{cite web |title=Max Verstappen looking set for F1 2020 at Red Bull |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11775650/max-verstappen-looking-set-for-f1-2020-at-red-bull |access-date=18 August 2022 |publisher=Sky Sports |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818170804/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11775650/max-verstappen-looking-set-for-f1-2020-at-red-bull |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Marko rates the best and worst traits of Red Bull's F1 stars |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-rates-the-best-and-worst-traits-of-red-bulls-f1-stars/10334712/amp/ |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=Autosport |date=8 July 2022 |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818170804/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-rates-the-best-and-worst-traits-of-red-bulls-f1-stars/10334712/amp/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2021, three-time Formula One World Champion [[Jackie Stewart]] claimed that Verstappen is the fastest driver in Formula One, but he also added that Verstappen is still in the "puppy stage" of his career.<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 September 2021|title=Verstappen now 'fastest driver in the business', Jackie Stewart claims|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/formula1/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-jackie-stewart-f1-b1921212.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220512/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/formula1/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-jackie-stewart-f1-b1921212.html |archive-date=12 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2022|website=The Independent}}</ref> [[Peter Windsor]], an experienced Formula One journalist, expressed Verstappen's ability to change direction "quicker than anybody else" through the high-speed section Maggots and Becketts: Silverstone's fastest sequence of corners. Windsor stressed that Verstappen's lightning-quick change of direction is a result of the innate feel he has for creating the "perfect platform" to achieve what he wants with the car during a lap. He is intrinsically able to create, for "a trillionth of a second", a minuscule "flat area" between the left and the right of a change of direction ahead of him, in order to attain a stable balance with the car before applying the next steering and throttle input.<ref>{{Citation|title=If Max is an early braker why is he so fast? By Peter Windsor| date=22 July 2021 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M7AgJXQ2rEI|access-date=13 January 2022|archive-date=11 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111082058/https://www.youtube.com/watch?app=desktop&v=M7AgJXQ2rEI|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]]'s team principal, [[Franz Tost]], declared Verstappen to be the fastest driver in Formula One; following the Dutchman's "really deserved" maiden title triumph in 2021.<ref name="Woodhouse2021">{{cite news |last=Woodhouse |first=Jamie |title=Franz Tost: 'Fastest driver' Max Verstappen deserved his Formula 1 world title |url=https://www.planetf1.com/news/franz-tost-max-verstappen-deserved-title |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=PlanetF1 |date=14 December 2021 |archive-date=6 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206183802/https://www.planetf1.com/news/franz-tost-max-verstappen-deserved-title/ |url-status=live}}</ref> After winning the {{F1|2024}} World Drivers' Championship in the third-placed [[Red Bull RB20|RB20]], James Elson of ''[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]]'' stated "if there was any doubt beforehand, 2024 proved that Max Verstappen is F1’s best driver", adding that "not only the fastest, capable of creating one-lap magic, he knows how to produce all it takes to win in the race too".<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2024-f1-drivers-ranked-is-verstappen-really-no1/ |title=2024 F1 drivers ranked: Is Verstappen really No1? |last=Elson |first=James |date=10 December 2024 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=10 December 2024 |issn=0027-2019}}</ref>

===Dominance over teammates===
[[File:Red Bull duo 2016 Malaysia Race.jpg|right|thumb|Verstappen ''(right)'' was teammates with [[Daniel Ricciardo]] ''(left)'' from {{F1|2016}} to {{F1|2018}}, pictured at the [[2016 Malaysian Grand Prix]].]]
Former Formula One driver [[Eddie Irvine]] praised Verstappen, stating that he is "by far the most dominant team leader on the grid." Irvine highlighted that Verstappen "has had many different second drivers in the team and none of them have got close to him."<ref name="Sharan2021Irvine">{{cite news |last=Sharan |first=Rahul |title=Irvine finds similarities between Verstappen and Schumacher |url=https://racingnews365.com/irvine-finds-similarities-between-verstappen-and-schumacher |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=RacingNews365 |date=10 June 2021 |archive-date=14 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210614105847/https://racingnews365.com/irvine-finds-similarities-between-verstappen-and-schumacher |url-status=live}}</ref> During the 2020 season, Jenson Button stated that he does not "think there's been a driver that's annihilated their teammates like he [Verstappen] has in a very long time."<ref>{{cite web|title=Button: Verstappen &quot;annihilating&quot; team-mates like Senna|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/button-verstappen-annihilating-team-mates-like-senna-4979817/4979817/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=25 August 2020 |archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113084508/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/button-verstappen-annihilating-team-mates-like-senna-4979817/4979817/|url-status=live}}</ref> Motorsport columnist and former Formula One driver [[Jolyon Palmer]], commented that Verstappen's maiden World Championship triumph could usher in a "new era of dominance" in the sport. Palmer wrote:<blockquote>[Verstappen's] qualifying pace is frightening and has been the basis for this title-charging campaign. He's had the most pole positions of anyone with 10 – almost half of the races, and it would have been half had he completed his mesmeric Jeddah lap, which ended up being possibly Max's biggest error in a near-perfect season. For a driver who has demolished three successive team mates in three years and made only a handful of small mistakes in that time, you question what scope {{sic|their}}  even is for improvement – but if he can take his game onto another level from here, we could be about to see the start of a new era of dominance.<ref>{{Cite web|title=PALMER: Whatever you thought of the Abu Dhabi outcome, Verstappen was a worthy champion in 2021|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.palmer-whatever-you-thought-of-the-abu-dhabi-outcome-verstappen-was-a-worthy.6RkHgJTJgx8HjlqwPraGo0.html|access-date=2022-01-27|publisher=Formula One |archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113090926/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.palmer-whatever-you-thought-of-the-abu-dhabi-outcome-verstappen-was-a-worthy.6RkHgJTJgx8HjlqwPraGo0.html|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote>Journalist Scott Mitchell expounded the reason why the Dutchman's teammates have fallen short "even with the data". Mitchell wrote: "Verstappen drives mainly on intuition, and that comes from years of training and preparation. He has a database in his head which he can use immediately. Even with data, Gasly and Albon could see where he was faster, but they could never grasp how he was faster there. That's because what makes Verstappen so good is mainly unconscious." According to Mitchell, those years of training and driving on his intuition has made it impossible for other drivers to measure up to Verstappen.<ref>{{Cite web|date=19 January 2021|title=Verstappen 'driving style' myth is a trait of greatness|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/verstappen-driving-style-myth-is-a-trait-of-greatness/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=The Race|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115064106/https://the-race.com/formula-1/verstappen-driving-style-myth-is-a-trait-of-greatness/|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Verstappen & Perez Chinese GP 2024.jpg|left|thumb|Verstappen ''(right)'' has been teammates with [[Sergio Pérez]] ''(left)'' since {{F1|2021}}, pictured at the [[2024 Chinese Grand Prix]].]]
Helmut Marko asserted that Verstappen's progress has moved him clear of his former Formula 1 team-mate Daniel Ricciardo, in both qualifying and race trim. "There is specific data," Marko told ''Autosport'', "In qualifying the gap to Ricciardo is greater. The strange thing is Max sometimes slides more, but still manages to keep the tyres alive." Verstappen previously mentioned that he was three or four-tenths faster on average than "very fast qualifier" Daniel Ricciardo.<ref>{{Cite web|last=GMM|date=28 September 2017|title=Max Verstappen says he's considerably faster than Red Bull F1 teammate Daniel Ricciardo|url=http://autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1831511/max-verstappen-says-hes-considerably-faster-red-bull-f1-teammate-daniel/|access-date=15 January 2022|website=Autoweek|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115065822/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1831511/max-verstappen-says-hes-considerably-faster-red-bull-f1-teammate-daniel/|url-status=live}}</ref> Marko concluded that then 20-year-old Verstappen "clearly moved away" from Ricciardo since the "second half of the 2018 season."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Marko: Verstappen moved clear of ex-Red Bull F1 team-mate Ricciardo|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-verstappen-moved-clear-of-ex-red-bull-f1-team-mate-ricciardo-5282660/5282660/|access-date=15 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=13 January 2019 |archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115032851/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-verstappen-moved-clear-of-ex-red-bull-f1-team-mate-ricciardo-5282660/5282660/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Natural talent===
