Following his maiden Formula One win, at the [[2016 Spanish Grand Prix]], three-time Formula One World Champion [[Niki Lauda]] described Verstappen as the "talent of the century."<ref>{{cite web|title=Niki Lauda calls Max Verstappen the 'talent of the century'|url=https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1846031/niki-lauda-calls-f1-driver-max-verstappen-talent-century/|website=autoweek.com|date=16 May 2016|access-date=28 January 2022|archive-date=28 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128125836/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1846031/niki-lauda-calls-f1-driver-max-verstappen-talent-century/|url-status=live}}</ref> Red Bull team principal Christian Horner stated that Verstappen is the best driver Red Bull have ever seen: "I have no doubt [Verstappen is] the best we have seen on one of our cars, in terms of outright raw ability and commitment. He's the best driver we've seen."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Horner on the 'rare' quality Verstappen shares with Hamilton |url=https://racingnews365.com/horner-on-the-rare-quality-verstappen-shares-with-hamilton |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=RacingNews365 |date=10 January 2022 |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818175204/https://racingnews365.com/horner-on-the-rare-quality-verstappen-shares-with-hamilton |url-status=live}}</ref>

Former Formula One driver [[Gerhard Berger]] echoed Jenson Button's recent comments, anointing Max Verstappen as the Formula One driver of this era with the most raw talent. Speaking to ''Sport1'', Berger ventured: "When it comes to raw talent, Max Verstappen is the most talented of all. But it's not just about raw talent, it's about the whole package. That means it's not just about setting the fastest laps but also to win a race. And not just [about] one race but many and eventually a championship, and championships."<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 June 2021|title=Berger: Verstappen probably has most raw talent of all|url=https://www.grandprix247.com/2021/06/15/gerhard-berger-says-when-it-comes-to-raw-talent-max-verstappen-is-probably-on-top-of-it-all/|access-date=8 January 2022|website=GRAND PRIX 247|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108010013/https://www.grandprix247.com/2021/06/15/gerhard-berger-says-when-it-comes-to-raw-talent-max-verstappen-is-probably-on-top-of-it-all/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Two-time Formula One World Champion Fernando Alonso commented that Verstappen is the standout driver in Formula One, declaring the Red Bull star to be "one step ahead" of everyone. Alonso noted that Verstappen deserved to win the Formula One drivers' championship in Abu Dhabi, ahead of the title decider that saw the Dutchman and Lewis Hamilton enter level on points: "Mercedes lately have been more performing and they've won a couple of races now, but Max is driving – in my opinion – one step ahead of all of us. We saw the [qualifying] lap in Jeddah, until he touched the wall at the last corner, that lap was coming from Max, not the Red Bull."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alonso believes Verstappen 'driving one step ahead of everyone' as he says Dutchman 'deserves' 2021 title|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.alonso-believes-verstappen-driving-one-step-ahead-of-everyone-as-he-says.2j28pfrHJJlpCfuykTmw0T.html|access-date=12 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=12 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220112054056/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.alonso-believes-verstappen-driving-one-step-ahead-of-everyone-as-he-says.2j28pfrHJJlpCfuykTmw0T.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Former Formula One driver [[Karun Chandhok]] likened Verstappen's ruthless and uncompromising attitude in race combat to Michael Schumacher's unyielding and iron-willed style of racing.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chandhok |first=Karun |title=Karun Chandhok's top 10 Formula 1 drivers of the 2021 season: Who makes the cut after epic year? |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/36347/12498220/karun-chandhoks-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-the-2021-season-who-makes-the-cut-after-epic-year |publisher=Sky Sports |access-date=18 December 2021 |archive-date=18 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218102740/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/36347/12498220/karun-chandhoks-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-the-2021-season-who-makes-the-cut-after-epic-year |url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen was ranked first in the annual Formula One team principals' top ten drivers ranking in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen tops Autosport's F1 team boss rankings for 2021|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-tops-autosports-f1-team-boss-rankings-for-2021/6886514/|access-date=17 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=18 December 2021 |archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108122236/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-tops-autosports-f1-team-boss-rankings-for-2021/6886514/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=REVEALED: F1's team bosses choose their Top 10 drivers of 2021|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.revealed-f1s-team-bosses-choose-their-top-10-drivers-of-2021.1sK8ysV0LK0MIbeNsHAkgY.html|access-date=17 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115200559/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.revealed-f1s-team-bosses-choose-their-top-10-drivers-of-2021.1sK8ysV0LK0MIbeNsHAkgY.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Racecraft===
[[File:Podium 2017 Malaysia.jpg|thumb|right|Verstappen ''(middle)'' on the podium with [[Lewis Hamilton]] ''(left)'' and [[Daniel Ricciardo]] ''(right)'' after winning the [[2017 Malaysian Grand Prix]]]]
Following Verstappen being given a warning for his driving conduct at the 2016 Belgian Grand Prix, the 18-year-old received the backing of then three-time champion Lewis Hamilton, who commented: "firstly, give the guy a break, he is 18 years old. What the frickin' heck were any of us doing at 18?"<ref>{{cite web |title=Verstappen Welcomes Support From Hamilton |url=https://news.sky.com/story/verstappen-welcomes-support-from-hamilton-10567203 |publisher=Sky News |date=6 September 2016 |access-date=12 January 2022 |archive-date=5 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205015109/https://news.sky.com/story/verstappen-welcomes-support-from-hamilton-10567203 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Despite earning high praise and acclaim from Formula One drivers and experts in and out of the sport, Verstappen faced criticism in the wake of the penalties he incurred during the [[2021 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix]]. Following this race, former Formula One driver [[Martin Brundle]] wrote: "Such is [his] car control and cunning, he's sometimes able to pull off the audacious moves and leave a margin of doubt as to whether it's hard racing or simply a professional foul outside of the regulations and it's those moments which are generating the confusion, controversies and inconsistencies. [[Ayrton Senna]] and Michael Schumacher had their faults too, and I was on the receiving end from both of them on occasions, but it's a sizeable dent on their immense reputations, not a positive."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Martin Brundle: Max Verstappen must stop these tactics vs Lewis Hamilton for his legacy... but what a title showdown we'll have|url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/12488713/martin-brundle-max-verstappen-must-stop-these-tactics-vs-lewis-hamilton-for-his-legacy-but-what-a-title-showdown-well-have|access-date=9 January 2022|publisher=Sky Sports|archive-date=9 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220109043216/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/12488713/martin-brundle-max-verstappen-must-stop-these-tactics-vs-lewis-hamilton-for-his-legacy-but-what-a-title-showdown-well-have|url-status=live}}</ref> Following an impressive first half of the 2022 season, journalist [[David Tremayne]] claimed Verstappen had elevated himself to a new higher level compared to his 2021 title winning season, suggesting Verstappen's first title had made him more relaxed and "chirpy".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tremayne |first1=David |title=TREMAYNE: Why 2022 Max Verstappen is an upgrade on the 2021 version |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.tremayne-why-2022-max-verstappen-is-an-upgrade-on-the-2021-version.6ajpJsL1vXqlNQMzTiTbtL.html |publisher=Formula One |access-date=4 August 2022 |archive-date=4 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220804135531/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.tremayne-why-2022-max-verstappen-is-an-upgrade-on-the-2021-version.6ajpJsL1vXqlNQMzTiTbtL.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Following the [[2024 Mexico City Grand Prix]], Verstappen received widespread condemnation from fans and media for incidents involving title rival [[Lando Norris]], for which he received 20 seconds worth of time penalties.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/explained-why-the-stewards-decided-to-hit-verstappen-with-not-one-but-two.6oI6P7n0TDUKUC9215E8JW|title=EXPLAINED: Why the stewards decided to hit Verstappen with not one but two penalties in Mexico|publisher=Formula One|date=28 October 2024|access-date=30 October 2024|first=Lawrence|last=Barretto}}</ref> Many commentators and former drivers likened his tactics and 'win-at-all-costs' attitude to those of [[Ayrton Senna]] and [[Michael Schumacher]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f1oversteer.com/news/the-michael-schumacher-advice-jos-verstappen-gave-to-max-after-the-mexico-city-grand-prix/|title=The Michael Schumacher advice Jos Verstappen gave to Max after the Mexico City Grand Prix|website=F1 Oversteer|date=30 October 2024|access-date=30 October 2024|first=Rory|last=Mitchell}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/racing/f1/story/_/id/42043242/to-f1-surprise-max-verstappen-overstepped-mexico-city-grand-prix|website=ESPN|date=27 October 2024|access-date=30 October 2024|first=Nate|last=Saunders|title=To few in F1's surprise, Verstappen overstepped in Mexico}}</ref> whilst {{F1|1996}} World Drivers' Champion [[Damon Hill]] characterised them as reminiscent of ''[[Wacky Races]]'' antagonist [[Dick Dastardly]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/cvge8n9yzdlo|work=BBC Sport|date=30 October 2024|access-date=30 October 2024|title='Dick Dastardly' tactics – Hill criticises Verstappen|first=Bobbie|last=Jackson}}</ref> Before the following race in [[2024 São Paulo Grand Prix|São Paulo]], Verstappen criticised the alleged British bias in the media, stating "I have the wrong passport".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-i-have-the-wrong-passport-for-the-f1-paddock/10668853/|title=Verstappen: I have the wrong passport for the F1 paddock|first=Filip|last=Cleeren|date=1 November 2024|access-date=4 November 2024|website=Autosport}}</ref> Upon his victory from 17th on the grid in the rain-affected race, he stated in the post-race press conference "I appreciate all of you being here, but I don't see any British press. Do they have to run to the airport, or [do they not] know where the press conference is?"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/max-verstappen-f1-johnny-herbert-damon-hill-norris-b2640841.html|title=Max Verstappen calls out 'British press' after wet-weather masterclass in Brazil|first=Philip|last=Duncan|date=4 November 2024|access-date=4 November 2024|work=The Independent}}</ref>

===Fan support===
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2021 Post-Race Scene.jpg|thumb|right|The Verstappen grandstand at the [[2021 Austrian Grand Prix]]]]
Verstappen has accumulated a significant fanbase from around the world, particularly from his home country of the Netherlands. The frequent association of Verstappen with the colour [[orange (colour)|orange]]—the [[national colour]] of the Netherlands—has led to his fanbase being referred to as the ''Orange Army''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/28/f1-max-verstappen-will-not-forget-win-in-front-of-adoring-orange-army|work=The Guardian|date=28 August 2023|last=Richards|first=Giles|access-date=16 October 2024|title=Max Verstappen adds to highlight reel in front of his adoring orange army}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/303938/max-verstappen-on-the-support-of-the-orange-army.html|website=GPBlog|date=29 September 2024|last=Crothall|first=Sophia|access-date=16 October 2024|title=Verstappen 'wouldn't wish pressure' from Orange Army on anyone}}</ref>

Several races across Europe have dedicated Verstappen [[grandstand]]s to accommodate thousands of travelling Dutch fans, boosting ticket sales at Grands Prix such as in [[Belgian Grand Prix|Belgium]], [[Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]] and [[Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]].<ref name="Smith 2018">{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Luke |title=The Max Factor: How Verstappen's fans have changed F1 |website=Crash |date=26 August 2018 |url=https://www.crash.net/f1/feature/904148/1/max-factor-how-verstappens-fans-have-changed-f1 |access-date=9 February 2022 |archive-date=9 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220209210247/https://www.crash.net/f1/feature/904148/1/max-factor-how-verstappens-fans-have-changed-f1 |url-status=live}}</ref> A Verstappen grandstand featured at the inaugural [[Las Vegas Grand Prix]] in [[2023 Las Vegas Grand Prix|2023]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.verstappen.com/en/article/5092/|website=Verstappen.com|date=11 May 2023|title=Exclusive Max Verstappen Grandstand at the Las Vegas Grand Prix 2023|last=Hendrix|first=Niels|access-date=16 October 2024}}</ref>

During the [[2021 Dutch Grand Prix]], the managing director of [[Honda in Formula One]], {{ill|Masashi Yamamoto (motorsport)|lt=Masashi Yamamoto|ja|山本雅史 (モータースポーツ)}}, praised Verstappen's support, stating that "in the six years I've been involved with Honda F1, I've never seen such a great turnout as at the Dutch Grand Prix. It was like being in a football stadium."<ref name="gpblog.com 2022">{{cite web |title=Honda impressed by Verstappen fans: 'Never seen such a great turnout' |website=gpblog.com |date=2 January 2022 |url=https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/102453/honda-impressed-by-verstappen-fans-never-seen-such-a-great-turnout.html |access-date=24 March 2022 |archive-date=23 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220223034800/https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/102453/honda-impressed-by-verstappen-fans-never-seen-such-a-great-turnout.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

In October 2021, Verstappen was voted the most popular Formula One driver in an official worldwide survey conducted by [[Nielsen Media Research]] and [[Motorsport Network]], earning 14.4% of the vote with particular success in the [[United States]] and [[Japan]].<ref name="Galloway 2021">{{cite web |last=Galloway |first=James |title=F1 fan survey lists Max Verstappen as most-popular driver ahead of Lando Norris and Lewis Hamilton |publisher=Sky Sports |date=21 October 2021 |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12440256/f1-fan-survey-lists-max-verstappen-as-most-popular-driver-ahead-of-lando-norris-and-lewis-hamilton |access-date=24 March 2022 |archive-date=23 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220223012214/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12440256/f1-fan-survey-lists-max-verstappen-as-most-popular-driver-ahead-of-lando-norris-and-lewis-hamilton |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/new-global-fan-survey-reveals-f1s-most-popular-team-anddriver.2evqTWEPsWYeBlw9vmSyBs|title=New global fan survey reveals Formula 1's most popular team and driver|publisher=Formula One|date=21 October 2021|access-date=16 October 2024}}</ref>

The fan-made song "[[Super Max!]]", performed by the {{Ill|Pitstop Boys|nl}} in 2016, went viral after his victory at the [[2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]], topping the [[Spotify]] ''Viral 50'' chart in the Netherlands and reaching number two in the United Kingdom.<ref name="Gamble 2021">{{cite web |last=Gamble |first=Andrew |title=Verstappen's song 'Super Max' goes viral & enters Spotify's top charts |website=Daily Express |date=15 December 2021 |url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/f1-autosport/1536642/Max-Verstappen-F1-song-Super-Max-goes-viral-Spotify-top-charts |access-date=12 September 2022 |archive-date=26 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211226014407/https://www.express.co.uk/sport/f1-autosport/1536642/Max-Verstappen-F1-song-Super-Max-goes-viral-Spotify-top-charts |url-status=live}}</ref> Another fan-made [[Electronic dance music|EDM]] track "33 Max Verstappen", was released in 2023, eventually going viral on social media due to [[internet meme]]s referencing the hook: "tu tu tu du, Max Verstappen".<ref>{{cite news |title=The New Max Verstappen Anthem An Absolute Banger Taking Over All-Time Favorite Super Max |url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/f1-news-the-new-max-verstappen-anthem-an-absolute-banger-taking-over-all-time-favorite-super-max/ |last=Suhalka |first=Mahim |date=6 September 2022 |work=[[EssentiallySports]] |access-date=2 April 2024 |archive-date=2 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402122316/https://www.essentiallysports.com/f1-news-the-new-max-verstappen-anthem-an-absolute-banger-taking-over-all-time-favorite-super-max/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=On His Birthday, Max Verstappen's Big Spotify Hit Goes Missing |url=https://thesportsrush.com/f1-news-on-his-birthday-max-verstappens-big-spotify-hit-goes-missing/ |last=Gopal Srivastava |first=Naman |date=30 September 2023 |access-date=2 April 2024 |work=The Sports Rush |archive-date=2 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402122320/https://thesportsrush.com/f1-news-on-his-birthday-max-verstappens-big-spotify-hit-goes-missing/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Other racing ==
===Sportscar racing===
[[File:MSR_GTP_WGI23_11.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Acura ARX-06]] (pictured in 2023) tested by Verstappen with [[Honda Racing Corporation]] in November 2024.]]
Verstappen tested the [[Honda NSX (second generation)#Super GT|Honda NSX-GT]]—a [[Super GT#GT500|GT500]] class [[Super GT]] car—during the 2022 [[Honda Racing Corporation|Honda Racing]] ''Thanks Day'' event at [[Mobility Resort Motegi|Motegi]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Klein |first=Jamie |date=26 November 2022 |title=Verstappen samples Honda NSX-GT Super GT car |url=https://www.motorsport.com/supergt/news/verstappen-honda-nsx-motegi-test/10405164/ |access-date=30 November 2024 |website=[[Motorsport.com]]}}</ref> After winning the event's [[kart racing|kart race]] alongside [[Marc Márquez]], Honda awarded Verstappen—the first [[Honda in Formula One|Honda-powered]] World Drivers' Champion since {{F1|1991}}—with an [[Honda NSX (second generation)#NSX Type S (2022)|NSX Type S]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.verstappen.com/en/article/4987 |title=Max full of gratitude at Honda Racing Thanks Day: 'An incredible feeling'|website=Verstappen.com |date=28 November 2022 |access-date=30 November 2024 |first=Stefan |last=Meens}}</ref>

In January 2024, Verstappen drove the [[Ferrari 296 GT3]] at the [[Algarve International Circuit]] in [[Portimão]], as part of a two-day test with [[Deutsche Tourenwagen Masters]] team [[Emil Frey Racing]] alongside [[Thierry Vermeulen]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/dtm/news/why-verstappen-tested-a-ferrari-gt3-car-for-dtm-team-emil-frey/10563140/ |title=Why Verstappen tested a Ferrari GT3 car for DTM team Emil Frey |date=6 January 2024 |access-date=20 November 2024 |first=Sven |last=Haidinger |website=[[Autosport]]}}</ref> who competed under the ''Verstappen.com Racing'' banner in [[2023 Deutsche Tourenwagen Masters|2023]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.verstappen.com/en/article/5019|title=Thierry Vermeulen takes the next step to contest DTM |date=24 February 2023 |access-date=20 November 2024 |first=Niels |last=Hendrix |website=Verstappen.com}}</ref> Team principal Lorenz Frey-Hilti stated "there were also other [[Group GT3|GT3]] cars that day, but I can only say that Verstappen was driving on a different level than the rest. There are good drivers who cannot shine in a GT3 car due to a lack of experience, but Max is different. If something has four wheels, then [he's fast in it]", adding that he was "world-class".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://racingnews365.com/verstappen-amazes-dtm-teamboss-during-test-max-is-on-another-level |title=Verstappen amazes DTM team boss during test: 'Max is on another level' |date=8 January 2024 |access-date=20 November 2024 |first=Rory |last=Mitchell |website=RacingNews365}}</ref>

On 19 November 2024, Verstappen drove a [[Sports prototype|prototype]] for the first time, testing the [[Acura ARX-06]] with [[Honda Racing Corporation]] at [[Las Vegas Motor Speedway]], ahead of the {{F1GP|2024|Las Vegas}}.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.roadandtrack.com/news/a62953060/max-verstappen-will-drive-acuras-imsa-gtp-racer-today/ |title=Max Verstappen Will Drive Acura's IMSA GTP Racer Today |date=19 November 2024 |access-date=20 November 2024 |magazine=[[Road & Track]] |first=Fred |last=Smith}}</ref> Verstappen expressed his desire to compete in the [[24 Hours of Daytona]] and [[24 Hours of Le Mans|Le Mans]] after the test, stating that "it's just about finding the time".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/imsa/news/verstappen-eager-to-race-daytona-24-and-le-mans-after-gtp-car-test/10674741/ |title=Verstappen eager to race Daytona 24 and Le Mans after Acura run |last=Barnes |first=Joey |date=21 November 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |access-date=8 December 2024}}</ref>

===Sim racing===
In his free time, Verstappen competes in [[sim racing]]. Verstappen stated that it helps him with his real-life racing, keeping him "ready to go".<ref name="RacingNews365">{{cite web |title=How Verstappen uses sim racing to become a better driver |website=RacingNews365 |date=11 January 2022 |url=https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-uses-sim-racing-to-become-a-better-driver |access-date=16 January 2022 |archive-date=16 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220116135001/https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-uses-sim-racing-to-become-a-better-driver |url-status=live}}</ref> Since 2015, Verstappen has been a member of ''Team Redline'', a British-Luxembourgish multinational professional sim racing team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Team Redline › Max Verstappen|url=https://www.teamredline.com/work/max-verstappen/|access-date=22 January 2022|website=Team Redline|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122123254/https://www.teamredline.com/work/max-verstappen/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iracing.com/max-verstappen-joins-team-redline/|title=Max Verstappen Joins Team Redline|date=30 July 2015|access-date=24 November 2024|first=Jaime|last=Baker|website=[[iRacing]]}}</ref>

====iRacing Special Events (2020–present)====
{{see also|iRacing}}
[[File:Max Verstappen 2024 iRacing Daytona 24.jpg|thumb|right|Verstappen (pictured driving the [[Mercedes-AMG GT3]]) won the 2024 ''iRacing Daytona 24 Special Event'' in the [[IMSA SportsCar Championship#GT Daytona (GTD)|GTD]] class.]]
Verstappen has competed in several marquee events on ''[[iRacing]]'' since February 2019, when he entered the ''[[Mount Panorama|Bathurst]] 12 Special Event''—a 12-hour virtual team [[endurance racing (motorsport)|endurance race]]—alongside [[Lando Norris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autosport.com/esports/news/f1-duo-verstappen-and-norris-team-up-for-iracings-bathurst-12-hour-5283532/5283532/|title=F1 duo Verstappen and Norris team-up for iRacing's Bathurst 12 Hour|date=8 February 2019|access-date=26 November 2024|first=Andrew|last=van Leeuwen|website=[[Autosport]]}}</ref> The pair won the ''[[Spa-Francorchamps|Spa]] 24 Special Event'' in July.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/verstappen-and-norris-win-spa-24-hour-esports-race/|title=Verstappen and Norris win Spa 24-hour esports race|date=22 July 2019|access-date=26 November 2024|website=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]]|first=Jake|last=Williams-Smith}}</ref> Verstappen won the ''[[Petit Le Mans]] Special Event'' in October 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-race.com/gaming/verstappen-wallmeier-win-iracings-petit-le-mans-event/|title=Verstappen/Wallmeier win iRacing's Petit Le Mans event|date=4 October 2020|access-date=26 November 2024|first=Matt|last=Beer|website=The Race}}</ref> Later that year, [[Haas F1 Team|Haas]] driver and ''R8G eSports'' founder [[Romain Grosjean]] deemed Verstappen to be the "fastest" driver in sim racing.<ref>{{cite web|last=GPfans.com|title=Grosjean zou Verstappen wel in zijn sim-team willen: "Hij is het snelst"|url=https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/60667/grosjean-zou-verstappen-wel-in-zijn-sim-team-willen-hij-is-het-snelst/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=GPfans|date=21 December 2020 |language=nl|archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113111909/https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/60667/grosjean-zou-verstappen-wel-in-zijn-sim-team-willen-hij-is-het-snelst/|url-status=live}}</ref> He entered the eighth round of the 2023 ''AMX Global League'' at [[Imola Circuit|Imola]], winning the first heat.<ref name="ATK"/>

Verstappen entered the ''[[Daytona International Speedway|Daytona]] 24 Special Event'' in January 2024, winning the [[IMSA SportsCar Championship#GT Daytona (GTD)|GTD]] class with Redline.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/race/modern/esports-news--max-verstappen-wins-at-iracing-24-hours-of-daytona/|title=Esports News {{!}} Max Verstappen wins at iRacing 24 Hours of Daytona|date=23 January 2024|access-date=24 November 2024|first=Andrew|last=Evans|website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]]}}</ref> In May, Verstappen received media attention for entering the ''[[Nürburgring]] 24 Special Event'' on the same weekend as the {{F1GP|2024|Emilia Romagna}};<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/f1-news-max-verstappen-wins-24-hour-race-alongside-grand-prix-on-insane-weekend-01hy8mcjz6jb|title=F1 News: Max Verstappen Wins 24-Hour Race Alongside Grand Prix on Insane Weekend|date=19 May 2024|access-date=20 November 2024|first=Alex|last=Harrington|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]}}</ref> he won both events, achieving a [[List of Formula One driver records#Most consecutive pole positions|record-equalling]] eighth consecutive pole position at the latter. Following his victory at the former, Ed Hardy of ''[[Autosport]]'' opined that Verstappen had "firmly established himself as one of the best sim racers in the world".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autosport.com/le-mans/news/all-to-know-about-max-verstappens-sim-racing-career-amid-le-mans-24-hours-ambition/10613870/|title=All to know about Max Verstappen's sim racing career amid Le Mans 24 Hours ambition|date=22 May 2024|access-date=24 November 2024|first=Ed|last=Hardy|website=[[Autosport]]}}</ref> Verstappen won his second ''Spa 24 Special Event'' in July that year, completing a perfect season of 24-hour special events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://traxion.gg/max-verstappens-team-redline-win-24-hour-sim-racing-event-on-f1-weekend/|title=Max Verstappen's Team Redline win 24-hour sim racing event on F1 weekend|date=21 July 2024|access-date=24 November 2024|first=Thomas|last=Harrison-Lord|website=Traxion.GG}}</ref>

====Le Mans Virtual (2020–2023)====
{{see also|24 Hours of Le Mans Virtual|Le Mans Virtual Series|rFactor 2}}
Verstappen competed in the [[24 Hours of Le Mans Virtual]] on ''[[rFactor 2]]'' in [[2020 24 Hours of Le Mans Virtual|2020]], [[2022 24 Hours of Le Mans Virtual|2022]] and [[2023 24 Hours of Le Mans Virtual|2023]]—hosted by [[Automobile Club de l'Ouest]] and the [[FIA World Endurance Championship]]—as well as two further rounds of the [[2022–23 Le Mans Virtual Series]] in the [[LMP2]] class.<ref name="ATK">{{cite web|url=https://www.autosport.com/le-mans/news/all-to-know-about-max-verstappens-sim-racing-career-amid-le-mans-24-hours-ambition/10613870/|title=All to know about Max Verstappen's sim racing career amid Le Mans 24 Hours ambition|website=[[Autosport]]|date=22 May 2024|access-date=26 November 2024|first=Ed|last=Hardy}}</ref> He described the former competition as a "clown show" after a technical issue saw him retire from the lead of the 2023 edition,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/e-sports/esports/frustrated-verstappen-brands-virtual-le-mans-a-clown-show-was-it-justified/|title=Frustrated Verstappen brands Virtual Le Mans a 'clown show': was it justified?|date=16 January 2023|access-date=26 November 2024|first=Cambridge|last=Kisby}}</ref> subsequently finishing runner-up in the overall championship to [[Porsche in motorsport|Porsche Coanda]].<ref name="ATK"/>

==Personal life==
Verstappen holds [[dual citizenship|dual]] Dutch and Belgian citizenship, and decided to compete with a Dutch racing license, as his father [[Jos Verstappen|Jos]] did. He stated in 2014 that he "feels more Dutch", having spent more time with his father than with his mother during his childhood, as well as his upbringing in [[Maaseik]], a Belgian town at the Dutch border.<ref name="nationality2" /> The following year, Verstappen added that he "actually only lived in Belgium to sleep", and that he "was raised as a Dutch person and that's how [he feels]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gpfans.com/nl/artikelen/41751/dit-is-waarom-max-verstappen-niet-onder-de-belgische-vlag-rijdt/|title=Dit is waarom Max Verstappen niet onder de Belgische vlag rijdt|website=GPfans|date=3 July 2019 |access-date=1 November 2020|archive-date=19 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919153745/https://www.gpfans.com/nl/artikelen/41751/dit-is-waarom-max-verstappen-niet-onder-de-belgische-vlag-rijdt/|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2022, Verstappen stated that he appreciates both sides and is "half-half at the end of the day".{{citation needed|date=December 2024}}

He competed in Formula One for more than a season before obtaining a road driving licence on his 18th birthday.<ref>{{cite web|title=Road legal at last! Verstappen passes driving test on 18th birthday|url=http://www.formula1.com/content/fom-website/en/latest/headlines/2015/9/verstappen-passes-driving-test-on-18th-birthday.html|publisher=Formula One|access-date=30 September 2015|date=30 September 2015|archive-date=31 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731183946/http://www.formula1.com/content/fom-website/en/latest/headlines/2015/9/verstappen-passes-driving-test-on-18th-birthday.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen moved to [[Monaco]] the day after, in October 2015, and has lived there since and has said it was not for tax reasons.<ref name="GPNov15">{{cite news|url=http://www.grandprix.com/ns/ns32591.html|title=Verstappen moves out of home for Monaco|date=28 November 2015|work=GrandPrix.com|access-date=17 May 2016|archive-date=22 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160522214846/http://www.grandprix.com/ns/ns32591.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2020, Verstappen bought a [[Dassault Falcon 900]]EX aircraft from [[Virgin Galactic]]. The aircraft is [[aircraft registration|registered]] PH-DTF and operated by Exxaero.<ref name=Falcon>{{cite web |url=https://www.aviation24.be/tour-operators/exxaero/formula-one-racing-driver-max-verstappen-acquires-former-virgin-galactic-private-jet/ |title=Formula One racing driver Max Verstappen acquires former Virgin Galactic private jet |first=Bart |last=Noeth |publisher=Aviation24 |date=20 November 2021 |access-date=26 January 2022 |archive-date=26 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126173346/https://www.aviation24.be/tour-operators/exxaero/formula-one-racing-driver-max-verstappen-acquires-former-virgin-galactic-private-jet/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen is a supporter of [[FC Barcelona]] and [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Moerman |first=Christian |date=26 November 2021 |title=Verstappen over favoriete club FC Barcelona: 'Ik baalde van vertrek Koeman' |trans-title=Verstappen about favorite club FC Barcelona: "I was disappointed with the departure of Koeman" |url=https://www.f1maximaal.nl/max-verstappen/verstappen-over-favoriete-club-fc-barcelona-ik-baalde-van-vertrek-koeman |access-date=16 May 2022 |website=F1Maximaal.nl |language=nl |archive-date=31 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531140907/https://www.f1maximaal.nl/max-verstappen/verstappen-over-favoriete-club-fc-barcelona-ik-baalde-van-vertrek-koeman |url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen speaks three languages, Dutch, English and German, the latter of which he learned while karting with [[Michael Schumacher]].{{citation needed|date=December 2024}} In September 2022, he was appointed an Officer of the [[Order of Orange-Nassau]] in recognition of his racing achievements.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://nltimes.nl/2022/09/01/royal-honor-max-verstappen-appointed-officer-order-oranje-nassau|title=Royal honor for Max Verstappen: Appointed Officer in the Order of Oranje-Nassau|access-date=1 September 2022|date=1 September 2022|website=NL Times|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203401/https://nltimes.nl/2022/09/01/royal-honor-max-verstappen-appointed-officer-order-oranje-nassau|url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen has been dating [[Kelly Piquet]] since October 2020.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Bethânia Nunes |author2=Marina Ferreira |title=Modelo Kelly Piquet assume romance com piloto da Fórmula 1 Max Verstappen |url=https://www.metropoles.com/colunas/claudia-meireles/modelo-kelly-piquet-assume-romance-com-piloto-da-formula-1-max-verstappen |website=Metrópoles |access-date=13 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313152034/https://www.metropoles.com/colunas/claudia-meireles/modelo-kelly-piquet-assume-romance-com-piloto-da-formula-1-max-verstappen |archive-date=13 March 2021 |language=pt |date=1 January 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/pictures/max-verstappen-and-kelly-piquets-relationship-timeline/|website=Us Weekly|date=15 October 2024|access-date=2 November 2024|title=Max Verstappen and Kelly Piquet's Relationship Timeline|archive-date=15 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515125609/https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/pictures/max-verstappen-and-kelly-piquets-relationship-timeline/|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2024, they announced they were expecting their first child together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/42808964/max-verstappen-announces-girlfriend-kelly-piquet-pregnant |title=Max Verstappen announces girlfriend Kelly Piquet is pregnant |date=6 December 2024 |access-date=6 December 2024 |website=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=F1 champion Max Verstappen to become first-time father with girlfriend Kelly Piquet |url=https://apnews.com/article/max-verstappen-kelly-piquet-pregnant-a2821be92caa7541eb31c6268b83ee29 |access-date=6 December 2024 |date=6 December 2024 |website=[[AP News]]}}</ref>

